		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Nehor's Guild to cheep weapons<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, May 4th 1:36 PM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=2&mid=98899780231912&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=2&mid=98899780231912&num=0&post=1&replyto=98899780231912"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=98899780231912></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>You need not spend a lot of pp to be an effective rogue.&nbsp;&nbsp;However you do need to understand a few things about which attack do how much damage.  <br>Rogues have 3 main attacks.  Primary weapon, Backstab (lvl 10) and secondary weapon (lvl 13). AT lvl 10 normal attack and backstab do about the same amount of damage.  After lvl 15 you will do more damage with backstab than anyother attack.  Your seconday attack will account for about 40% of your normal damage.  <br><br>Magic Vs Nonmagic weapons.  90% of the time or more you will be fighting mobs that do not require a magic weapon to hit. At low lvl the only good loot that requires a magic weapon is a light stone.  In MHO the added cost of a magic weapon can not be justified at low lvls.  <br><br>Damage Vs Ratio<br>Until lvl 10 the ratio of the weapon will determain how much damage you do.  At lvl 10 the damage of your weapon will determain how much damage you do backstabing.  At lvl 13 the damage of your secondary weapon and the delay of your primary (as long as it is slower than the delay of the secondary weapon) will determain how much damage you do with your off-hand weapon.  By lvl 15 more than half the total damage done with your primary weapon will be from backstabing.  Therefore after lvl 15 the damage of the primary is more inportant than its ratio.  <br><br>Coments on rogue weapons:<br>The Dagger<br>Any 3 damage weapon is good for rasing skill and ok in the newbee.  However they don't do enough damage to use after lvl 10 as a primary or a secondary weapon.  If you have one with good stats put it in the range slot item.  <br>The Short Sword<br>Rusty daggers have the highest (worst) ration of any newbee weapon.  A short sowrd has as good of ratio as any rusty 1hs, and will rase your skill quickly.  For these weapons a low lvl rogue may want to use the Short Sword for killing and the dagger for rasing skill.  Tarnished short swords have the best ratio of any tarnished 1hs. Short Swords can be bought from vendors for about 3pp. Both the tarnished short and the short sword are fast enough to be used as off hand weapons. And do enough enough damage to be worth while.  <br>Crys knife (and other damage 4 weapons)<br>After lvl 10 these weapons have too low of damage to be used in the primary. Howerver they are fast and thus make good off hand weapons.  <br>Giant Snake Fang<br>In MHO this is a great weapon.  At damage 5 they do good backstabing damage and the 27 delay gives them a good ratio.  By lvl 10 any rogue should be able to kill a giant snake.  <br>Fine Steel Spear<br>This is the top of the line for cheep nonmagical rogue weapons.  The 6 damage is as good or better as many magical daggers.  Dual wilding these will do about the same damage as any magical 6 damage primary combanation.  They are cheep.  <br><br>Where and how to obtain the best knights for low lvl rogues. <br>Giant Snake Fangs:  These drop off snakes in most low lvl zones.  Blackburrow, North Ro and so on.  <br><br>Fine Steel<br>These weapons can be bought in a number of the old world zone.  South Karana, and Everfrost probly are the best zones to buy in.  <br><br>Drachnid Leg Tip<br>This weapon has the same stats as the FS Spear but is magical.  You can ride the boat to FV and acution to buy one of these.  Most people don't bring these back to sell to other players, and they should be very reasionable now.  <br><br>Bloodstained Fang<br>This is one of the best rogue weapons in the game and the best rogue weapon you can get with out spending major pp.  Some people don't like this weapon because of how slow it is.  Yes it is slow but it has a better ratio that the Dragoon Dirk, the Bloodclaw, and the Walrus Thooth.  And it ratio is almost as good as the Tomb Carver.  And it has great damage.  At lvl 20 you will be backstabing for 63hp vs 47 for a 6 damage weapon.  The long delay also let you use some higher damage off hand weapons like the frozen long sword.  These two weapon will out damage any other weapon combo you can get with out spending several hundred plat.  You can take the Boat to Ice clad and auction to buy these, or buy then at the igloo venders at 45pp.  Personaly I'm not giving up my Bloodstained fang until I can get a 10 damage or better weapon.  </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=2><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=2&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=2&mid=98899780231912&num=0&post=1&mid=98899780231912><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 class=mform><tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>0 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class2">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
